樂隊 

四撃頭敲擊樂團                        

Four Gig Heads Percussion Group




                            4gigheads.com                        










四撃頭敲擊樂團簡介

“四撃頭”敲擊樂團於98年成立，為香港青年敲擊樂演奏家符一中、周展彤、何怡安、及陸健斌所創立，現為藝術發展局一年支助團體。團員均畢業於香港演藝學院，主修中國敲擊樂，師隨著名敲擊樂演奏家、香港中樂團副團長及敲擊首席閻學敏先生，並邀得閻師任四撃頭之駐團藝術顧問。他們的成立，旨在推廣古今中外敲擊樂，譜寫、編配敲擊樂作品，藉以發揚中外敲擊樂文化，創造新音樂空間，並拓展香港的藝術領域。
“四撃頭”經常獲邀參與本港各類型文化表演活動，當中包括99年獲香港藝術節委約創作《打樂十八層之身體福音》，並擔任敲擊及舞蹈表演；98及02年在香港實驗劇場「進念二十面體」Zuni Icosahedron之作品《魔笛》及《百年孤寂》中擔任配樂及現場伴奏；00年應香港舞蹈團邀請參與「黃土、黃河」之編曲及現場伴奏；02及07年參與慶祝香港特別行政區成立五周年及十周年之「龍聲飛躍—萬人青年音樂會」及《龍聲鼓舞萬人青年音樂會》敲擊樂獨奏部份及領奏部份，分別都創下新健力士世界紀綠；04及06年獲香港中樂團邀請演出《鼓王羣英會》；08年於香港大學及中文大學之《四撃頭敲擊樂音樂會》; 09年於中華人民共和國成立六十週年慶祝活動中擔任表演嘉賓；城市當代舞蹈團07《蘭陵王》、09《非常道》。四撃頭亦經常獲邀參與世界各地多類型之文化藝術活動，包括遠赴英國倫敦、菲律賓及德國柏林參與當地藝術節之演出；01年於法國康城影展中擔任表演嘉賓；08年獲邀赴韓國參與3rd CheonAn-GakWon (華溪寺)International Temple Music(BumEum) Festival 之演出。
除在社會各層面作多類型之表演活動外，“四撃頭”亦積極推動香港音樂教育，包括到各學校舉行音樂會。該團曾擔任香港科技大學及香港大學之駐校藝術團體；2003年初獲香港電台邀請，出任第四台駐台演奏家。
“四撃頭”演奏的曲目豐富多採，除當代作曲家的敲擊樂作品外，還涉獵世界各地的民間樂曲，諸如京劇敲擊、浙東鑼鼓、湘西土家族打溜子、美國鄉村音樂及巴西森巴音樂等。如此兼擅中西古今的演奏風格在當今云云敲擊樂組合中實屬異數，四撃頭亦以此獨步樂壇，備受讚譽。
四擊頭獲邀為”Sabian”銅鈸商代言人。
香港藝術發展局支助團體。

Four Gig Heads is formed in 1998 by the local percussionists, Chau Chin Tung, Ho Yi-on, Angus Fu Ye Chung and Luk Kin-Bun, all graduates of the Hong Kong Academy for Performing Arts trained in Chinese percussion under Yim Hok-man, a famous percussionist and Deputy Concertmaster cum Percussion Principal of the Hong Kong Chinese Orchestra. The aim of the group is to promote percussion music of both east and west genres. The members also compose and arrange percussion music themselves to expand new dimensions for music as well as create a unique culture for Hong Kong. The group has often been invited to various types of cultural performances in Hong Kong, including the solo percussion section of The Music of the Dragons Concert and Dragon Jamboree in celebration of the 5th and 10th Anniversaries of the Hong Kong SAR in 2002 and 2007, arrangement of music and delivery of live accompaniment at the Hong Kong Dance Company’s 2000 production, The Yellow River & The Yellow Earth, and production of score and live performance for the Hong Kong experimental theatre group, Zuni Icosahedron, in their 1998 production of The Magic Flute and the 2002 production of One Hundred Years of Solitude Version 9.0. In 1999, the group was commissioned by the Hong Kong Arts Festival to compose for a performance, Boombastic Verses, in which they played the percussion and danced. The group was also involved in solo performance in Majestic Drums by the Hong Kong Chinese Orchestra in 2004 and 2006. Four Gig Heads has often been invited to attend international cultural activities, including performances at the arts festivals in London, the Philippines and Berlin. It was also a guest performer at the 2001 Cannes Film Festival. In 2008, invited by Korea “3rd CheonAn-GakWon International Temple Music(BumEum) Festival” to be a guess performer. In addition to giving a wide variety of performances, Four Gig Heads is also dedicated to the promotion of music education in Hong Kong. It has given many educational concerts in schools, and has been an Artist-in-Residence at the Hong Kong University of Science and Technology and the University of Hong Kong. It was also an Artist-in-Residence of RTHK in 2003. Four Gig Heads has a versatile repertoire encompassing an impressive array of styles, including Peking opera percussion music, gong-and-drum music of eastern Zhejiang, the daliuzi of the Tujia ethnic minority of western Hunan, American country music, Brazilian samba, as well as works by leading contemporary composers. The group is credited for its ability to embrace different musical traditions and forges a unique place among percussion ensembles today. Four Gig Heads is the endorser for “Sabian” cymbal since 2007. And is financially supported by Hong Kong Arts Development Council.
 



